                        "id": "builder-238a10598dd446c69f1c86591f7b0a46",
                        "component": {
                          "name": "Copy",
                          "options": {
                            "rawHtml": "<p>\n  As blockchain networks, Ethereum and Solana possess unique data structures,\n  functioning as global public world computers that store and share data on\n  their networks. In this chapter, we aim to explore how these chains structure\n  their data sets.\n</p>\n"
                          }
                        },
