          {
            "@type": "@builder.io/sdk:Element",
            "@version": 2,
            "id": "builder-b50bf9832862417f90d78a9912c4bc74",
            "properties": {
              "id": "account-ethereum"
            },
            "meta": {
              "previousId": "builder-da4caf072e5c46c892e31e77fba40b97",
              "localizedTextInputs": ["rawHtml"]
            },
            "component": {
              "name": "Copy",
              "options": {
                "rawHtml": "<h3><strong>'Account' in Ethereum</strong></h3><p>In Ethereum, an 'account' refers to an entity that owns Ether and can send transactions. It includes addresses necessary for deposits and withdrawals and is categorized as follows:</p><ul><li><strong>EOA (Externally Owned Account): </strong>An account owned externally, possessing a private key. Think of it as an account for an individual's wallet.</li><li><strong>CA (Contract Account):</strong> An account for contracts, holding smart contract code.</li></ul><p>A key difference between EOA and CA in Ethereum is that EOA, not being a smart contract, typically does not have its own storage. Therefore, the code hash of an EOA is set to a 'null' hash, indicating that the account does not have storage.</p><p>An Externally Owned Account (EOA) is an account with a private key, and possessing a private key means controlling access to funds or contracts. The private key implies control over access to funds or contracts. The following data are included in an EOA:</p>"
              }
            },
            "responsiveStyles": {
              "large": {
                "display": "flex",
                "flexDirection": "column",
                "position": "relative",
                "flexShrink": "0",
                "boxSizing": "border-box",
                "paddingTop": "20px"
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "@builder.io/sdk:Element",
            "@version": 2,
            "id": "builder-d1299a0f7b6848dfbd4523073f7f69a0",
            "meta": {
              "previousId": "builder-8844dbb2364c4c71a3a035b54e727755"
            },
            "component": {
              "name": "Custom Code",
              "options": {
                "code": "<style type=\"text/css\">\n  table.custom{\n      width: 100%;\n  }\n  table.custom thead td{\n      font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  table.custom td{\n      padding: 8px 10px;\n      border: 1px solid #414141;\n  }\n  table.custom .gray{\n      background-color: #424242;\n  }\n  table.custom .green{\n      background-color: rgba(180, 251, 221, 0.7);\n\n  }\n  table.custom .red{\n      background-color: rgba(255, 117, 74, 0.7);\n  }\n  table.custom .yellow{\n      background-color: rgba(232, 241, 128, 0.7)\n  }\n</style>\n<table class=\"custom\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Field</td>\n      <td>Description</td>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>address</code></td>\n      <td><p>An Account’s address</p></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>balance</code></td>\n      <td><p>The amount of ETH (in wei) an address owns.</p></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>nonce</code></td>\n      <td>\n        <p>\n          A counter that shows the number of transactions sent from the account\n          to ensure transactions are processed only once. with smart contracts,\n          it reflects the number of contracts created by the account.\n        </p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>code hash</code></td>\n      <td><p>The code of an account on the EVM.</p></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>storage hash (storage root)</code></td>\n      <td>\n        <p>\n          A 256-bit hash of the root node of a Merkle Patricia Tree that encodes\n          the storage contents of the account. This tree encodes the hash of the\n          storage contents of this account, and is empty by default.\n        </p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n",
                "scriptsClientOnly": true
              }
            },
            "responsiveStyles": {
              "large": {
                "display": "flex",
                "flexDirection": "column",
                "position": "relative",
                "flexShrink": "0",
                "boxSizing": "border-box",
                "paddingRight": "50px",
                "paddingLeft": "50px",
